commentary: Starc to Stokes, OUT that is too good! It was going to take something outstanding to dislodge Stokes, and Starc serves it up with an impeccable off-stump yorker, tailing back in wickedly as it zeroed in on the base of the pole! He kicks his bat away in disgust, but he's done everything he can to keep England alive ...

commentary: Behrendorff to Ali, OUT edged and gone! Moeen's shocking run can't end today, a perfect response. Moeen had to look to be assertive, but that ball wasn't there to be attacked, and he was beaten before his stroke could fully take shape

commentary: Behrendorff to Woakes, OUT a massive wipe over the leg side, but what a catch! Woakes thought he had nailed it, in the arc, a huge heave, but Maxwell tracked back on the edge of the rope, hopped to pouch the ball high above his head, then, cool as you like, lobbed it back to the waiting Finch to complete a routine relay! England, as if you didn't already know it, are sunk without trace in this one!
